Gary B. Smith


Obituary
Condolences
Gallery


































 Smith, Gary B.Brighton: June 4, 2017. Predeceased by parents, Anne and John Smith; and in-laws, John and Marian Sullivan. Survived by wife, Kathleen (Sullivan) and children, Kerrie (Sean) Mullen, Kyle, Kate, Kevin, Kelly, and Kristen as well as treasured grandson, Rory Michael Mullen. Also survived by siblings, James Smith, Janet Smith, Patricia (John) Carlson, Gregory (Allison) Smith, and Marcia Smith; many nieces and nephews.Friends may call Thursday, June 8, 3-5 PM and 7-9 PM at the funeral chapel (2305 Monroe Ave.). A Mass of Christian Burial will take place Friday, June 9, 10 AM at Our Lady of Lourdes Roman Catholic Church, 150 Varinna Dr., Rochester. Interment at Holy Sepulchre Cemetery. Please direct memorial donations to McQuaid Jesuit High School, Our Lady of Mercy School for Young Women, Our Lady of Victory/St. Joseph Church or the Women's Care Center (womenscarecenterfoundation.org). To share a memory of Gary or send a condolence to the family visit www.anthonychapels.com.



Published in Rochester Democrat And Chronicle on June 6, 2017


